    <item>
      <title>Jingyu Lee</title>
      <link>https://jingyulee.com/authors/admin/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 25 Mar 2024 02:32:30 +0900</pubDate>
      <guid>https://jingyulee.com/authors/admin/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;Hi! I&amp;rsquo;m a Ph.D. student at the &lt;a href=&#34;https://hcs.snu.ac.kr&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;Human-Centered Computer Systems Lab&lt;/a&gt; under the supervision of professor &lt;a href=&#34;https://youngkilee.blogspot.com&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;Youngki Lee&lt;/a&gt;.
I build a &lt;a href=&#34;https://band.snu.ac.kr&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;software platform&lt;/a&gt; for edge devices that enable real-time mixed reality applications for everyone.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I have previous research experiences in medical image processing and deep learning from my masters at &lt;a href=&#34;https://chungmy.github.io&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;Deep Learning and Image Processing Group&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=&#34;http://cglab.snu.ac.kr&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;Computer Graphics and Image Processing Lab&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I was an enthusiastic game engine developer graduated from DigiPen Institute of Technology and worked for &lt;a href=&#34;https://education.minecraft.net&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;Minecraft: Education Edition&lt;/a&gt; at Microsoft Studios.&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
